Total IP Control v1.1.1 - Release Notes
Copyright (c) 2026 Sysop Network

Thank you for installing Total IP Control, centralized IP management,
proxy detection, connection control, and audit logging for The Major
BBS v10.

What's new in this release:
  * Fixed: refused connections no longer record a "SEND error 10038
    (Socket operation on non-socket)" in the audit trail. Connections
    refused by "Require trusted proxy" (or the pre-login connection
    limit) are now turned away before the connection is handed to the
    telnet daemon, so nothing is written to the closed socket. This
    also removes stray characters that could follow the refusal
    message.
  * Audit logging is now a four-way choice, cycled with the space bar:
    NO, AUDIT, LOG, or BOTH. It controls two independent destinations
    -- the BBS Audit Trail (the live sysop log) and the daily log
    files under TOTALIPCONTROL\. NO logs nothing, AUDIT writes only
    the trail, LOG writes only the files, and BOTH writes both.
  * New login access log. A dedicated TOTALIPCONTROL\LOGINS\ folder
    records who connected and from where -- one line per successful
    login, for every protocol (telnet, SSH, and others), with the date
    and time, user ID, real IP address, and protocol.
  * SSH server module compatibility. "Require trusted proxy (block
    direct)" now applies to telnet only; SSH, Rlogin, and other
    daemons are no longer refused by it. Connection limiting, audit
    logging, GeoIP location, and profile IP recording still apply to
    those connections.

Installing:
  1. Copy SNTIPCTL.DLL, SNTIPCTL.MDF, and SNTIPCTL.MSG into your BBS
     installation directory (typically C:\BBSV10).
  2. Restart the BBS. Total IP Control prints its version and active
     feature set to the startup log.
  3. Sign on as a user holding the MASTER key and run /TOTALIP to
     configure the module. All features are off by default.

Upgrading from an earlier version:
  1. Stop the BBS.
  2. Replace SNTIPCTL.DLL, SNTIPCTL.MDF, and SNTIPCTL.MSG with the
     files from this package.
  3. Restart the BBS. Your existing settings are preserved and the
     settings file is upgraded automatically on first start; no
     reconfiguration is required.

  If you are replacing the older PROXCLIP or IPControl modules, remove
  their entries from wgserv.cfg.

Notes for this upgrade:
  * If "Audit logging" was previously enabled, it is carried forward
    as BOTH (Audit Trail plus log files), matching the prior behavior.
  * The new TOTALIPCONTROL\LOGINS\ folder appears once file logging is
    enabled (LOG or BOTH).
  * If you run an SSH server module alongside Total IP Control, its
    connections are no longer blocked by "Require trusted proxy."

